I think it is disappointing that a company the size of google would so blatantly spread misinformation and propagate cultural appropriation. The Spring Festival, which has historically been called Chinese New Year in the West, has been based on the Chinese Lunisolar calendar. This festival, among many others, based on the use of the Chinese lunisolar calendar have spread throughout Asia, but has never been called “Lunar New Year.” The sudden switch to Lunar New Year, and worse, Korean New Year, shows a desire to wipe the contributions of ancient Chinese scholars from the history books and attribute their great contributions to an “allied country.” It’s shameful and short sighted. Regardless of current geopolitics, to try to rewrite such fundamental history is deeply disappointing for a company that’s founded on providing relevant information to consumers.
